Principal 
Investment Strategies
 
The Fund 
seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in the equity 
securities (common stocks, preferred stocks and convertible securities) of small 
capitalization U.S. companies. The Fund defines small capitalization (small cap) 
companies as those with a market capitalization of no more than $2 billion at 
the time of purchase. Under normal circumstances, the Fund will invest at least 
80% of its assets (for the purpose of this requirement, net assets includes net 
assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities of 
companies with small market capitalization. The Fund is non-diversified, which 
means that it can invest a greater percentage of its assets in any one issuer 
than a diversified fund.
 


  


